📖 Data Catalog
1. Source Systems
The data is ingested from two primary source systems in CSV format:

ERP (Enterprise Resource Planning): Contains core operational data including product details, categories, and subcategories.

CRM (Customer Relationship Management): Contains customer-facing data including personal details, demographics (from web surveys), and sales transactions.

2. Bronze Layer (Raw Objects)
Table Name	Source System	Description
bronze.crm_cust_info	CRM	Raw customer identity data (names, IDs, birthdates).
bronze.crm_sales_details	CRM	Raw transaction records (order numbers, dates, amounts).
bronze.crm_item_info	CRM	Raw product catalog with basic pricing.
bronze.erp_loc_a101	ERP	Customer geographic/location data (Area A101).
bronze.erp_cust_az12	ERP	Supplementary customer demographic data.
bronze.erp_px_cat_g1v2	ERP	Product categorization and hierarchy.
3. Silver Layer (Cleaned & Standardized)
Table Name	Transformations Applied
silver.crm_cust_info	Removed duplicates, standardized gender ('M'/'F'), handled NULLs.
silver.crm_sales_details	Formatted dates, ensured positive sales values, cleaned ID keys.
silver.erp_loc_a101	Normalized region names and cleaned city casing.
silver.erp_px_cat_g1v2	Trimmed whitespace and standardized category naming conventions.
4. Gold Layer (Dimensional Model)
The Gold layer represents the Star Schema used for final reporting.

Dimension Tables
gold.dim_customers: Master table for customer attributes.

Key Columns: customer_key, customer_id, full_name, gender, country.

gold.dim_products: Master table for product hierarchy.

Key Columns: product_key, product_name, category, subcategory, cost.

Fact Tables
gold.fact_sales: Central fact table containing quantitative business metrics.

Key Columns: order_number, customer_key, product_key, order_date.

Metrics: sales_amount, quantity, price.

5. Metadata & Data Quality Rules
Update Frequency: Full Refresh (Truncate & Load).

Business Rules: * Transactions with sales amount ≤0 are excluded or flagged.

Customers without a valid ID in both CRM and ERP are handled via specific join logic.

Date format is standardized to YYYY-MM-DD.
